<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-11T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="538" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/470b: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-11T17:00:00-05:00">December 11, 1930—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>428. For the Minister: The Department’s 419, December 8, 5 p.m.<note n="79" xml:id="d538fn1">Telegram not printed.</note></p>
                        <p>Department has been informed by Minister Wu that a copy of the Chinese
                            Government’s counter proposals, as presented to the Department by
                            Minister Wu on December 7, has been handed to you. Please telegraph the
                            differences between the text thereof and the text of the counter
                            proposals handed, as reported by you,<note n="79" xml:id="d538fn2">Telegram not printed.</note> to the British Minister on December
                            1.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>